4. Ba4 { The goal of this move is to remove the a6 Pawn threat and continue to put pressure on the Black Knight on the diagonal leading to the King. This variation is called Columbus. } { [%cal Ra4c6] } 4... b5 { Black can reply with b5 (Caro variation) forcing the White Bishop to move Bb3 with a good diagonal on the weak pawn f7. } { [%cal Rb5a4] } 5. Bb3 { White moving Bb3 remove the b5 Black Pawn threat making pressure on weak f7 Black Pawn. } { [%cal Rb3f7] } *


