{ The Closed Variation is a continuation of the Columbus Variation where instead of b5 Black play Nf6. }
5... Nf6 { Black play Nf6 to threaten White Pawn in e4 and defend the d5 square. White protects the King with a castle. } { [%cal Rf6e4,Gf6d5] } 6. O-O { White King is protected and Black prepares for a similar move. } 6... Be7 { Black move Bb7 to prepare its King to castle. } *


